# Frontend Development Rules

## Overview

The frontend is a React + TypeScript application built with Vite. It uses TailwindCSS for styling with full RTL support, Zustand for state management, and WebSocket for real-time agent communication.

---

## Tech Stack

- **React 18** with TypeScript
- **Vite** for build tooling
- **TailwindCSS** for styling
- **Zustand** for state management
- **WebSocket** for agent communication

---

## Project Structure

```
frontend/src/
├── App.tsx                 # Main app component
├── main.tsx               # Entry point
├── index.css              # Tailwind + global styles
├── components/            # UI components
│   ├── SessionPanel/      # Session sidebar
│   ├── Chat/              # Chat interface
│   └── PromptBox/         # Input component
└── shared/                # Shared utilities
    ├── auth/              # Auth module (internal store)
    ├── websocket/         # WebSocket service
    ├── hooks/             # Shared hooks
    ├── api/               # REST API client
    ├── constants/         # Constants
    └── utils/             # Utilities (cn, etc.)
```

---

## RTL Support

This app supports Hebrew (RTL). Follow these rules strictly:

### Use Logical Properties

**NEVER use physical properties for directional styling:**

| ❌ Physical | ✅ Logical | Meaning |
|-------------|-----------|---------|
| `ml-4` | `ms-4` | margin-inline-start |
| `mr-4` | `me-4` | margin-inline-end |
| `pl-4` | `ps-4` | padding-inline-start |
| `pr-4` | `pe-4` | padding-inline-end |
| `left-0` | `start-0` | inset-inline-start |
| `right-0` | `end-0` | inset-inline-end |
| `text-left` | `text-start` | text-align: start |
| `text-right` | `text-end` | text-align: end |
| `rounded-l-*` | `rounded-s-*` | border-start-radius |
| `rounded-r-*` | `rounded-e-*` | border-end-radius |
| `border-l-*` | `border-s-*` | border-inline-start |
| `border-r-*` | `border-e-*` | border-inline-end |

### Flexbox Handles RTL Automatically

Use `justify-start` and `justify-end` - they flip automatically in RTL:

```tsx
// User messages - on the END side
<div className="flex justify-end">
  <div className="rounded-ee-md">User message</div>
</div>

// Assistant messages - on the START side
<div className="flex justify-start">
  <div className="rounded-es-md">Assistant message</div>
</div>
```

### Icons That Need Flipping

Some icons should mirror in RTL (arrows, send, logout):

```tsx
<Send className="h-5 w-5 rtl:scale-x-[-1]" />
<LogOut className="h-4 w-4 rtl:scale-x-[-1]" />
```

