## Module Patterns

### Auth Module

The auth module has an internal Zustand store. Only export the hook:

```tsx
// shared/auth/index.ts - only exports useAuth
export { useAuth } from "./useAuth";

// Usage
const { managerId, login, logout } = useAuth();
```

### WebSocket Module

WebSocket service is a singleton. Use the exported instance:

```tsx
import { wsService } from "@/shared/websocket";

wsService.connect();
wsService.setAuthToken(managerId);
wsService.joinSession({ shift_plan_id: sessionId });
wsService.sendChatMessage(sessionId, message);
```

### API Module

Use the API functions for REST calls:

```tsx
import { getSessions, createSession } from "@/shared/api";

const sessions = await getSessions(managerId);
const newSession = await createSession({ manager_id: managerId });
```

---

## Component Patterns

### Props Interface

Define props interface above the component:

```tsx
interface ChatProps {
  sessionId: number | null;
  className?: string;
}

export function Chat({ sessionId, className }: ChatProps) {
  // ...
}
```

### Use `cn()` for Class Names

Always use `cn()` from utils for conditional classes:

```tsx
import { cn } from "@/shared/utils";

<div className={cn(
  "base-classes",
  condition && "conditional-classes",
  className
)} />
```

### Stable Function References

Use `useCallback` for functions passed to children:

```tsx
const handleSubmit = useCallback((text: string) => {
  sendMessage(text);
}, [sendMessage]);
```

---

## State Management

### Local State

Use `useState` for component-local state.

### Shared State

Use hooks from `shared/hooks/` for shared state:

```tsx
const { sessions, create, remove } = useSessions(managerId);
const { messages, sendMessage } = useChatState(sessionId);
```

### Global State

Auth state is global via Zustand (internal to auth module).

---

## File Naming

- Components: PascalCase (`SessionPanel.tsx`)
- Hooks: camelCase with `use` prefix (`useChatState.ts`)
- Utils/constants: camelCase (`websocket.ts`)
- Index files: `index.ts` for barrel exports

---

## Imports

Use path aliases:

```tsx
import { cn } from "@/shared/utils";
import { useAuth } from "@/shared/auth";
import { Chat } from "@/components/Chat";
```

---

## Error Handling

Handle errors explicitly and show user-friendly messages:

```tsx
try {
  await createSession(params);
} catch (err) {
  setError(err instanceof Error ? err.message : "Failed to create session");
}
```

---

## Quick Checklist

- [ ] Using logical properties (ms-, me-, ps-, pe-, start-, end-)
- [ ] Using `cn()` for class merging
- [ ] Using `useCallback` for handlers passed to children
- [ ] Errors handled and displayed to user
- [ ] Hebrew text for UI labels
- [ ] Icons that need flipping have `rtl:scale-x-[-1]`
